{"TopicId":176154,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Are Lagrange points possible in KSP?","CreatedByName":"Dr. SpaceFreak","CreatedById":188271,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T20:02:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dr. SpaceFreak","CreatedById":188271,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T20:02:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was thinking in launching a couple of missions recreating\u00A0 SOHO and a SENTINEL for asteroid tracking, and some orbital telescopes from a mod, but I think these points aren\u0027t possible in KSP because of the physics in the game, am I right? If it\u0027s not possible, is there an alternative for these points where a probe can be in Kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E and also be aligned with Kerbin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-24T20:03:44Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2018 08:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Dr. SpaceFreak\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T20:11:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223404735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529870527\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188271\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dr. SpaceFreak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/24/2018 at 1:02 PM, Dr. SpaceFreak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... and some orbital telescopes from a mod, but I think these points aren\u0027t possible in KSP because of the physics in the game, am I right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSort of yes, and sort of no. True Lagrange points require 3-body physics, which stock KSP does not do. However, since you already have modded your game, there are mods you can add that will allow n-body physics -- and therefore Lagrange points.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/24/2018 at 1:02 PM, Dr. SpaceFreak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is an alternative for these points where a probe can be in Kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E and also be aligned with Kerbin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the point of Lagrange points is that they are \u0022stable\u0022 -- or metastable, at least.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nL3 (opposite side of the sun, same orbit), L4, or\u00A0L5 (60 degrees behind and ahead of a celestial body in the same orbit) in the stock game will give you metastable orbits of the correct period.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. SpaceFreak","CreatedById":188271,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T20:16:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223404746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529871112\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, since you already have modded your game, there are mods you can add that will allow n-body physics -- and therefore Lagrange points.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the answer!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, which are those mods?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T20:26:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223404749\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529871416\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188271\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dr. SpaceFreak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/24/2018 at 1:16 PM, Dr. SpaceFreak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the answer!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, which are those mods?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe one I know about is Principia.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsEmbed_finishedLoading\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5395656472\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/162200-wip131-143-principia%E2%80%94version-dedekind-released-2018-06-13%E2%80%94n-body-and-extended-body-gravitation-axial-tilt\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022overflow: hidden; height: 225px; max-width: 502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ArmoredLipid","CreatedById":189824,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T23:02:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry using those mods to make trojans out of asteroids.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}